obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (2950)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent, application and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00002_195012_1517807320273&sectionId=2950&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00002_195012_1517807320273
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Emblems`
  line `and Names (Prevention of Improper Use) Act, 1950.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1* * * and also applies to citizens of India outside India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by the Jammu and Kashmir (Extension of Laws) Act, 1956`
  line `(62 of 1956), s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line
  line `2. 1st September, 1950, see Gazette of India, 1950, Part II, s. 3`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (2951)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00002_195012_1517807320273&sectionId=2951&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00002_195012_1517807320273
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "emblem" means any emblem, seal, flag, insignia, coat-of-arms or pictorial representation`
  line `specified in the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(b) "competent authority" means any authority competent under any law for the time being in`
  line `force to register any company, firm, or other body of persons or any trade mark or design or to grant a`
  line patent;
  line
  line `(c) "name" includes any abbreviation of a name.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (2952)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Prohibition of improper use of certain emblems and names.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00002_195012_1517807320273&sectionId=2952&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00002_195012_1517807320273
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any law for the time being in force, no person shall, except in such cases and under such`
  line `conditions as may be prescribed by the Central Government, use or continue to use, for the purpose of any`
  line `trade, business, calling or profession, or in the title of any patent, or in any trade mark or design, any`
  line `name or emblem specified in the Schedule or any colourable imitation thereof without the previous`
  line `permission of the Central Government or such officer of Government as may be authorised in this behalf`
  line `by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (2953)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Prohibition of registration of certain companies, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00002_195012_1517807320273&sectionId=2953&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00002_195012_1517807320273
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in any law for the time being in force, no competent authority shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) register any company, firm or other body of persons which bears any name, or`
  line
  line `(b) register a trade mark or design which bears any emblem or name, or`
  line
  line `(c) grant a patent in respect of any invention which bears a title containing any emblem or name,`
  line
  line `if the use of such name or emblem is in contravention of section 3.`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises before a competent authority whether any emblem is an emblem specified in`
  line `the Schedule or a colourable imitation thereof, the competent authority may refer the question to the`
  line `Central Government, and the decision of the Central Government thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (2954)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title Penalty.
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00002_195012_1517807320273&sectionId=2954&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00002_195012_1517807320273
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Any person who contravenes the provisions of section 3 shall be punishable with fine`
  line `which may extend to five hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (2955)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Previous sanction for prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00002_195012_1517807320273&sectionId=2955&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00002_195012_1517807320273
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution for any offence punishable under this Act`
  line `shall be instituted, except with the previous sanction of the Central Government or of any officer`
  line `authorised in this behalf by general or special order of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (2956)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00002_195012_1517807320273&sectionId=2956&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00002_195012_1517807320273
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall exempt any person from any suit or other proceeding which`
  line `might, apart from this Act be brought against him.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (2957)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power of the Central Government to amend the Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00002_195012_1517807320273&sectionId=2957&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00002_195012_1517807320273
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, add to or alter the Schedule, and any such addition or alteration shall`
  line `have effect as if it has been made by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (2958)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00002_195012_1517807320273&sectionId=2958&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00002_195012_1517807320273
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 9 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-5-1986`
